description: A photon's energy is equal to its frequency multiplied by the Planck constant, and the wavelength of a matter wave equals the Planck constant divided by the associated particle momentum.

Fast InvSqrt() or by the hexadecimal constant 0x5F3759DF, is an algorithm that estimates  \( \frac{1}{\sqrt{x}} \), the reciprocal (or multiplicative inverse) of the square root of a 32-bit floating-point number \( x \) in IEEE 754 floating-point format.
Ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter.
